    "Antibiotics": {
      "text": "Treatment can be delayed for up to 9 days and still prevent major sequelae\nPenicillin\nOptions:\n[6]\nPenicillin V\n250mg PO BID x 10d (child) or 500mg BID x 10d (adolescent or adult)\nBicillin L-A\n<27 kg: 0.6 million units; ≥27 kg: 1.2 million units IM x 1\nAmoxicillin\n500-875 mg PO q12h or 250-500 PO q8h for 10d\n[7]\nPenicillin\nallergic (mild):\n[6]\nCefuroxime\n10mg/kg PO QID x 10d (child) or 250mg PO BID x 4d\nCefixime\n400mg/day PO in single daily dose x10d or divided q12hr x10d\nPenicillin\nallergic (anaphylaxis):\n[6]\nClindamycin\n7.5mg/kg PO QID x 10d (child) or 450mg PO TID x 10d OR\nAzithromycin\n12mg/kg QD (child) or 500mg on day 1; then 250mg on days 2-5",
      "subsections": {
        "Steroids": {
          "text": "Consider single dose of\ndexamethasone\n0.6mg/kg PO (Max = 10mg)\n[8]",
